			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Converter gas, also known as basic oxygen furnace gas or BOF gas, is a by-product gas produced during the steelmaking process in a basic oxygen furnace (BOF). This gas primarily consists of carbon monoxide (CO), carbon dioxide (CO2), and nitrogen (N2), with small amounts of hydrogen (H2) and other trace gases. It is generated when pure oxygen is blown into the furnace to convert molten iron into steel by oxidizing impurities such as silicon, manganese, and carbon. Converter gas is often collected and used as a fuel in various parts of the steel mill, contributing to energy recovery and efficiency in the steelmaking process.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">转炉气，亦称为基本氧气炉煤气或BOF煤气，是在基本氧气炉（BOF）中炼钢过程中产生的副产品气体。该气体主要由一氧化碳（CO）、二氧化碳（CO2）和氮气（N2）组成，还含有少量的氢气（H2）和其他痕量气体。当纯氧气吹入炉内，将熔融铁转化为钢时，通过氧化杂质如硅、锰和碳等，便会产生转炉煤气。转炉煤气通常被收集并用作钢铁厂各个部分的燃料，有助于炼钢过程中的能量回收和效率提升。</common:generalComment>
